Subject: [PATCH] dkms: include every module with unique array indices

DKMS requires every module array index from zero through the highest index to
exist. Add the missing gc5035 module, separate the imx471 and s5k3j1 entries,
and shift the later entries so all kernel-version branches remain contiguous.
Remove the obsolete CLEAN setting, which current DKMS ignores with a warning.

--- a/dkms.conf
+++ b/dkms.conf
@@ -5 +4,0 @@
-CLEAN="make KERNELRELEASE=$kernelver KERNEL_SRC=$kernel_source_dir clean"
@@ -66,0 +66,4 @@
+BUILT_MODULE_NAME[6]="gc5035"
+BUILT_MODULE_LOCATION[6]="drivers/media/i2c"
+DEST_MODULE_LOCATION[6]="/updates"
+
@@ -69,3 +72,3 @@
-    BUILT_MODULE_NAME[6]="ov05c10"
-    BUILT_MODULE_LOCATION[6]="drivers/media/i2c"
-    DEST_MODULE_LOCATION[6]="/updates"
+    BUILT_MODULE_NAME[7]="ov05c10"
+    BUILT_MODULE_LOCATION[7]="drivers/media/i2c"
+    DEST_MODULE_LOCATION[7]="/updates"
@@ -75,3 +78,3 @@
